flowRoot.flowPara: Notes can be stored locally on this device, on an email account, or through ownCloud. If you change accounts, your existing notes will be copied over.

text.tspan: Or you can just keep your notes on this device

flowRoot.flowPara: Storage location dialog lists online accounts that can be used to store notes. Configure accounts show the username/email address.
If the checkbox is selected, the list goes insensitive.
Selecting a list row for an unconfigured account initiates account setup. For configured accounts, a settings dialog is displayed.
If the storage location is changed, existing notes are silently copied over in the background. Notes are insensitive until they have been copied over.
Notes can be stored locally, on an email account, or through ownCloud. Additional storage locations can be added through the online accounts settings.
Please confirm the new location for your notes.
Your existing notes will be moved to the new location.
Next button becomes sensitive if the storage option is changed.
Add to the rest of your notes
The connection with angela@cloud.gnome.org has been lost. Move will resume when the connection has been reestablished.
If the network connection is lost during import, pause and wait for the user to reconnect.
Select where you want to import notes from.
Notes in supported applications and online accounts are automatically detected and listed. If no notes are found at these locations, only "Select Folder..." is shown as an option.
The import button becomes sensitive once an option is selected.
The connection with angela@cloud.gnome.org has been lost. Import will resume when the connection has been reestablished.
If the network connection is lost during import, pause and wait for the user to reconnect.
